- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper describes an algorithmic version of the Griffiths-Dwork method for the creative telescoping of rational functions.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper provides complexity results for the algorithm.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the logical structure of differential equations.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions a prototype implementation, which could potentially involve computational geometry techniques.
